        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="print">Down, | Beckenham, Kent. | Railway Station | Orpington. S.E.R.</hi></placeName>
                    <date>Feb. 28. 1877</date>
                    <salute>Dear Sir,</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>I thank you sincerely for your great kindness in having sent me your fine work on the Fossil Arctic Flora.<ref target="#foot.f1"/> It forms a valuable addition to the many similar gifts with which you have honoured me</p>
<p>Dear Sir | With my thanks &amp; high respect | Yours faithfully | Charles Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

            
            
        </div>

        

        

        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">Heer evidently sent volume 4 of <hi rend="italic">Flora fossilis arctica</hi> (<ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_3491.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Heer 1868–83</ref>), published in 1877; CD’s copies of volumes 3–6 are in the Darwin Library–CUL.</note>
        </div>        
            
